---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Terms of Use — Fractune">
  <nav class="nav">
    <div class="nav-inner">
      <a href="/" class="nav-logo"><img src="/logo.png" alt="" class="nav-logo-icon" />Fractune</a>
    </div>
  </nav>

  <main class="page">
    <div class="page-inner">
      <h1>Terms of Use</h1>
      <p class="last-updated">Version 1.0 — April 2026</p>

      <h2>1. Scope</h2>
      <p>
        These terms apply to your use of the Fractune mobile application ("the App")
        and the website at fractune.dk ("the Website"), collectively referred to as
        "the Service". The App is available on the Apple App Store. The agreement for
        the App is between you and Fractune (Colours by Barslund), not Apple. The App
        is licensed, not sold, to you.
      </p>

      <h2>2. The Service</h2>
      <p>
        Fractune is a fractal fluence analysis tool for building facades. The App
        calculates a fractal dimension (D-value) using the box-counting method and
        contributes analysis results to a publicly accessible dataset.
      </p>

      <h2>3. Contributions to the Public Dataset</h2>
      <p>
        By analysing a building with location sharing enabled, you agree that the
        analysis results — including D-value, metadata, and coordinates — will be
        published as part of the public dataset and made available at
        <a href="https://sites.fractune.dk">sites.fractune.dk</a>.
      </p>
      <p>
