        copyright. By contributing, you grant Fractune a perpetual, worldwide,
        royalty-free, non-exclusive licence to use, display, distribute, and sublicence
        your contributions as part of the public dataset.
      </p>

      <h2>4. User Eligibility</h2>
      <p>
        There is no minimum age restriction for using Fractune. However, we recommend
        that users under the age of 13 obtain parental or guardian consent before using
        the Service.
      </p>

      <h2>5. Acceptable Use</h2>
      <p>You agree not to:</p>
      <ol>
        <li>Submit false, fabricated, or deliberately manipulated analysis data.</li>
        <li>Overload or abuse the API or backend infrastructure.</li>
        <li>Attempt to identify, de-anonymise, or contact other contributors.</li>
        <li>Scrape or bulk-download the public dataset without permission.</li>
        <li>Use the dataset to train AI or machine learning models without prior written permission from Fractune.</li>
      </ol>

      <h2>6. Intellectual Property</h2>
      <p>
        The App, Website, algorithms, design, and all associated intellectual property
        are owned by Fractune / Anders Barslund. Analysis results (D-values and
        associated metadata) are factual measurements and are considered to be in the
        public domain.
      </p>

      <h2>7. Dataset Licence</h2>
      <p>
        Analysis data in the public dataset is made available under the terms of the
        separate <a href="/license">Dataset Licence</a>. By using data from the dataset,
        you agree to the terms set forth in that licence.
      </p>

      <h2>8. Disclaimer</h2>
      <p>
        The Service is provided "as is" and "as available" without warranty of any kind,
        whether express or implied, including but not limited to warranties of
        merchantability, fitness for a particular purpose, and non-infringement. D-values
        are mathematical approximations and should not be used as the sole basis for
        professional, scientific, or regulatory decisions. Apple Inc. expressly disclaims
        all warranties with respect to the App.
      </p>

      <h2>9. Limitation of Liability</h2>
      <p>
        To the maximum extent permitted by applicable law, Fractune shall not be liable
        for any indirect, incidental, special, consequential, or punitive damages arising
        out of or in connection with your use of the Service. Apple Inc. is not
        responsible for the App or its content and shall have no obligation to address
